Colin Shearing was convicted of indecent assault on a six-year-old girl in the 1980s . 
  He was sentenced to three years in jail at Swansea Crown Court but failed to turn up to be sentenced . 
  Shearing, 70, fled across the Channel to Paris to avoid being jailed for sex attack . 
  He booked himself into the Hotel des Nations in Paris before moving to a second and third hotel to evade police . 
  European arrest warrant has been issued for Shearing . 
 